Severn Trent Plc (SVT) , the U.K.â€™s second-largest publicly traded water company, awarded a three-year
sewer and maintenance contract valued at 30 million pounds
($46.4 million) to  May Gurney Integrated Services Plc. (MAYG)   May Gurney said today in a statement that the new Severn
Trent Water contract is one of three totalling 80 million pounds
recently awarded to the U.K. company by water utilities. May
Gurney is the fourth-largest municipal waste-collection service
provider in the U.K. and helps maintain roads and railways.  To contact the reporter on this story:
